        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 1:55PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Marshall, or 7 miles southwest of Hot Springs, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall, Hot Springs, Allenstand, Walnut, Spring Creek, Max Patch,
and Luck.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
